@page "/"

<div class="container py-4">
    <h1 class="display-5">Thesis Collaboration Workspace</h1>
    <p class="lead">
        This starter experience wires up the core infrastructure for supervising professors and thesis students.
        Hook the Blazor UI to MediatR commands to manage student workspaces, track progress updates, and schedule meetings.
    </p>

    <section class="mt-4">
        <h3>What’s ready</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Domain entities for students, professors, thesis projects, updates, and meetings</li>
            <li>CQRS commands &amp; queries to create projects, submit updates, schedule meetings, and fetch workspace dashboards</li>
            <li>EF Core persistence with repositories and validation pipeline behaviors</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
        <h3>Next steps</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Create Blazor components that invoke <code>CreateThesisProjectCommand</code>, <code>SubmitThesisUpdateCommand</code>, and <code>ScheduleMeetingCommand</code></li>
            <li>Design a professor dashboard that consumes <code>GetWorkspaceOverviewQuery</code></li>
            <li>Swap the in-memory database for SQL Server and add blob storage for file uploads</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
</div>
